Fahrenheit /ˈfærənˌhaɪt/

1. ADJ Fahrenheit is a scale for measuring temperature, in which water freezes at 32 degrees and boils at 212 degrees. It is represented by the symbol °F. 华氏的 [n/num ADJ] 

例： By mid-morning, the temperature was already above 100 degrees Fahrenheit. 到上午10点左右，气温已超过华氏100度了。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Fahrenheit is also a noun. 华氏温标 

例： He was asked for the boiling point of water in Fahrenheit. 有人问他华氏温标下水的沸点。

